# i18n Patterns

## Translation Structure

All translations live in `src/translations/index.js` as a flat object with nested keys:

```js
export const translations = {
  nav: {
    home: { en: 'Home', bg: 'Начало' },
    ...
  },
  seo: {
    title: { en: '...', bg: '...' },
    ...
  }
}
```

Every translatable string is an object with `en` and `bg` keys.

## Using Translations

```jsx
import { useLanguage } from '../contexts/LanguageContext'
import { translations } from '../translations'

const { t } = useLanguage()
const text = t(translations.section.key)
```

`t()` returns the string for the current language, falling back to `en`.

## LanguageContext

- Provider wraps the entire app
- State persisted to `localStorage` as `trendLang`
- `document.documentElement.lang` updated on change

## Adding New Translations

1. Add keys to `translations` in `src/translations/index.js`
2. Use `t(translations.section.newKey)` in the component
3. For new pages, add SEO keys under `translations.seo`

## Pricing

Display EUR only. Services data in `services.json` contains both EUR and BGN but only EUR is shown.

## Contact Translations

Phone, Viber, and call button text are under `translations.contact`:
- `contact.viber` -- Viber chat button text
- `contact.callBtn` -- Call button text
